<inglise> COMMISSION DECISION No 379/84/ECSC of 15 February 1984 defining the powers of officials and agents of the Commission instructed to carry out the checks provided for in the ECSC Treaty and decisions taken in application thereof </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI OTSUS nr 379/84/EST&Uuml;, millega m&auml;&auml;ratletakse komisjoni ametnike ja esindajate volitused, kes on ette valmistatud EST&Uuml; asutamislepingus ja selle rakendamisel tehtud otsustes s&auml;testatud kontrollimiste tegemiseks 15. veebruar 1984 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Coal and Steel Community, and in particular Article 47 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa S&ouml;e- ja Terase&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 47 ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary to define the scope of the powers to obtain information and carry out checks provided for in the first paragraph of Article 47 of the Treaty, without prejudice to the rights and powers referred to in the fourth paragraph of Article 86; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja m&auml;&auml;ratleda asutamislepingu artikli 47 esimeses l&otilde;igus s&auml;testatud volituste ulatus seoses info saamise ja kontrollimiste korraldamisega, ilma et see piiraks artikli 86 neljandas l&otilde;igus nimetatud &otilde;iguste ja volituste kohaldamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is the task of the Commission to ensure that the objectives set out in the Treaty are attained, and in particular that undertakings fulfil the obligations imposed on them by the provisions of the Treaty and the decisions taken in application thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni &uuml;lesanne on tagada asutamislepingus s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rkide t&auml;itmine ning eelk&otilde;ige ettev&otilde;tjatele pandud kohustuste t&auml;itmine asutamislepingu s&auml;tete ja selle rakendamiseks tehtud otsuste kohaselt; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in order to determine whether undertakings are acting in accordance with such obligations, it is necessary to carry out physical inspections and checks on their books; </inglise>
<eesti> selleks, et selgitada v&auml;lja, kas ettev&otilde;tjate tegevus on koosk&otilde;las nimetatud kohustustega, on tarvis teha f&uuml;&uuml;silisi kontrollimisi ning kontrollida ettev&otilde;tjate raamatupidamisdokumente; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas such checks and inspections can be effective only if the facts and operations of which the Commission may need to have cognisance can be ascertained from undertakings' business records, including records held in automated systems of any kind; whereas the use of data-processing techniques is likely to facilitate the execution of the inspections for both parties; </inglise>
<eesti> nimetatud kontrollimine ja inspekteerimine saab t&otilde;hus olla ainult siis, kui asjaolusid ja tegevust, mis v&otilde;ivad komisjonile vajalikuks osutuda, saab teha kindlaks ettev&otilde;tjate &auml;ridokumentide, k.a iga liiki automatiseeritud s&uuml;steemides sisalduvate dokumentide p&otilde;hjal; andmet&ouml;&ouml;tlusv&otilde;tted muudavad inspekteerimise t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt h&otilde;lpsamaks m&otilde;lemale poolele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas undertakings must not be allowed to evade their obligations with regard to inspections by depositing their business records away from the undertaking; whereas they must therefore also permit access to such records in these cases; </inglise>
<eesti> ettev&otilde;tjatele ei tohi anda v&otilde;imalust inspekteerimisega seotud kohustustest k&otilde;rvale hoida &auml;ridokumentide hoiuleandmisega ettev&otilde;ttest v&auml;ljapoole; ettev&otilde;tjad peavad ka k&otilde;nealustel juhtudel v&otilde;imaldama juurdep&auml;&auml;su sellistele dokumentidele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is not always possible to evaluate the material inspected whilst on the undertaking's premises and in such cases it is necessary to make copies or photocopies of or take extracts from the books or business records concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> alati ei ole v&otilde;imalik inspekteeritavat materjali hinnata ettev&otilde;tja t&ouml;&ouml;ruumides ning sellisel juhul on tarvis teha &auml;rakirju v&otilde;i valguskoopiaid v&otilde;i v&auml;ljav&otilde;tteid asjaomastest raamatupidamis- v&otilde;i &auml;ridokumentidest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in order for inspections to be rapid and effective, undertakings' managers or representatives should be required to give oral explanations on the spot to the officials or agents of the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> inspekteerimise kiiruse ja t&otilde;hususe huvides peaks saama n&otilde;uda, et ettev&otilde;tjate juhid v&otilde;i esindajad annaksid komisjoni ametnikele v&otilde;i esindajatele suulisi selgitusi kohapeal; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, to ensure that all required information is collected, the Commission's officials or agents must be allowed to enter any premises, land or means of transport of the undertaking concerned, and of any third party with whom its books or business records have been deposited, and in so doing to have sight of the said books and business records so as to be able to select all those that are relevant and are to be produced for inspection; </inglise>
<eesti> tagamaks kogu vajaliku info kogumist, peab komisjoni ametnikel v&otilde;i esindajatel olema luba siseneda asjaomase ettev&otilde;tja k&otilde;ikidesse t&ouml;&ouml;ruumidesse, transpordivahenditesse ja territooriumidele ning iga kolmanda isiku t&ouml;&ouml;ruumidesse, transpordivahenditesse ja territooriumidele, kelle juures ettev&otilde;tja raamatupidamis- ja &auml;ridokumente hoitakse, et oleks v&otilde;imalik nendega tutvuda ja v&auml;lja valida k&otilde;ik asjakohased dokumendid ning esitada need inspekteerimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order that inspections can be conducted efficiently, undertakings must actively assist the Commission's officials or agents in carrying out their duties; </inglise>
<eesti> inspekteerimiste t&otilde;hususe huvides peavad ettev&otilde;tjad komisjoni ametnikke v&otilde;i esindajaid nende kohustuste t&auml;itmisel aktiivselt abistama; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the information required may be determined only according to the purpose for which the check in question is intended; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;utava info kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramisel l&auml;htutakse ainult k&otilde;nealuse kontrollimise eesm&auml;rgist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas checks should be allowed to proceed rapidly, smoothly and without interruption; whereas they should therefore be possible upon simple production of an authorization in writing from the Commission, without an individual decision being required for this purpose; </inglise>
<eesti> kontrollimisi peab saama teha kiiresti, t&otilde;rgete ja katkestusteta; seet&otilde;ttu peaks neid saama teha ainult komisjoni kirjaliku loa alusel, ilma et selleks oleks vaja &uuml;ksikotsust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this Decision is without prejudice to the various other Decisions in force concerning inspections, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev otsus ei piira muude inspekteerimist k&auml;sitlevate kehtivate otsuste kohaldamist, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Officials and agents of the Commission instructed to carry out the checks on undertakings provided for in the first paragraph of Article 47 of the Treaty are hereby empowered: </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni ametnikel ja esindajatel, kes on saanud ettevalmistuse asutamislepingu artikli 47 esimeses l&otilde;igus s&auml;testatud kontrollimiste tegemiseks ettev&otilde;tjates, on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) to examine books and business records to the extent necessary for the purpose of the check, including records held in automated systems of any kind, wherever such books or business records are kept; </inglise>
<eesti> a) kontrollida raamatupidamis- ja &auml;ridokumente, sh mis tahes automatiseeritud andmeid, kontrollimiseks vajalikus ulatuses, olenemata raamatupidamis- v&otilde;i &auml;ridokumentide asukohast; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) to take copies or photocopies of or extracts from the books and business records, including data stored in automated systems of any kind; (c) to require oral explanations on the spot; </inglise>
<eesti> b) teha &auml;rakirju v&otilde;i valguskoopiaid v&otilde;i v&auml;ljav&otilde;tteid raamatupidamis- ja &auml;ridokumentidest, k.a mis tahes liiki automatiseeritud s&uuml;steemidesse salvestatud andmetest; c) n&otilde;uda kohapeal suulisi selgitusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) to enter any premises, land or means of transport of undertakings, and of any third party with whom books or business records have been deposited, and in so doing to have sight of the said books and business records so as to be able to select all those that are relevant and are to be produced for inspection. </inglise>
<eesti> d) siseneda k&otilde;ikidesse t&ouml;&ouml;ruumidesse, transpordivahenditesse v&otilde;i territooriumitele, mis kuuluvad ettev&otilde;tjatele v&otilde;i mis tahes kolmandale isikule, kelle juures raamatupidamis- v&otilde;i &auml;ridokumente hoitakse ning sel viisil tutvuda k&otilde;nealuste raamatupidamis- ja &auml;ridokumentidega, mis v&otilde;imaldab k&otilde;ik asjakohased dokumendid v&auml;lja valida ja inspekteerimiseks esitada. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Undertakings shall assist officials and agents of the Commission in carrying out their duties. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tjad abistavad komisjoni ametnikke ja esindajaid nende kohustuste t&auml;itmisel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Officials and agents of the Commission instructed to carry out checks shall exercise their powers upon production of an authorization in writing specifying the purpose of the check. </inglise>
<eesti> Kontrollimisteks ettevalmistatud komisjoni ametnikud ja esindajad t&auml;idavad oma kohustusi, esitades kirjaliku volituse, kus on nimetatud kontrollimise eesm&auml;rk. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Undertakings shall comply with the obligations imposed by Article 1 of this Decision without an individual decision being required for that purpose, failure to do so rendering them liable to the fines and penalties provided for in the third paragraph of Article 47 of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tjad t&auml;idavad k&auml;esoleva otsuse artiklis 1 etten&auml;htud kohustusi, ilma et selleks oleks vaja &uuml;ksikotsust ning selle n&otilde;ude t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise puhul rakendatakse nende suhtes asutamislepingu artikli 47 kolmandas l&otilde;igus s&auml;testatud trahve ja karistusi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 15 February 1984. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 15. veebruar 1984 </eesti>
<inglise> For the Commission Frans ANDRIESSEN Member of the Commission </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni nimel komisjoni liige Frans ANDRIESSEN </eesti>
 